This package contains the GIZA++ toolkit and the mkcls tool, originally
written by F.J. Och and several other authors.

For more information, refer to the README files and the following pages:
  http://www.fjoch.com/mkcls.html
  http://www.fjoch.com/GIZA++.html

Jonathan Graehl (Jun 2015): merge hznlp/giza-kn kneser-ney smoothing -
paper at http://www3.nd.edu/~dchiang/papers/zhang-acl14.pdf suggests
+1 BLEU and +3 F-score if you use new parameters (default = enabled!)

Hieu Hoang suggests mgiza - it's multi-threaded and resumable:
   https://github.com/moses-smt/mgiza
